#: 21337012-0-2756
msgctxt "21337012-0-2756"
msgid "I was to become a Razor Master, to replace the one I helped topple. For me, stepping through the Gate was like falling through a crucible of flame.\n\nIt burned deep, boiled my blood, and I crashed out in a field, amidst a shower of molten rock and steam. I don't know how it was that I lived.\n\nI realized I was clutching a dagger in my hand.\n\n""I have given you a means of defense."" The voice spoke, but no one was there.\n\n""This is all?"" I asked the air.\n\n""That is all you need. Now prove yourself, and live. Or fail, and embrace a new day."""
msgstr ""

#: 51188213-0-2756
msgctxt "51188213-0-2756"
msgid "The First Day"
msgstr ""

#: 21337012-0-2755
msgctxt "21337012-0-2755"
msgid "Today there was a wind—a fiery wind, above Red-Zeal Keep. I thought it was more of the Deadlands' wretched weather, but a massive form emerged from it, much taller than man or even mer, its great form trailing ash. It hung from nothing in the air.\n\nSome kind of procession followed, of all kinds of Daedric creatures, towards the Keep. They walked straight through pools of lava. Some couldn't survive the heat, but they marched on, burning and crackling as they went, prostrating themselves at the feet of that celestial object. There, they smoldered like a hundred miniature suns until they were no longer there. Days ago, this would have pleased me, but I believe these creatures do not wholly perish. I have seen too many of the same faces after I have smashed them, over and over again.\n\nThen came the Titan, landing in a crushing mass, and with it a rain of fire so fierce I swear the cave mouth, where I stood watching above, burned wider. I withdrew into darkness for a desperate pause, thinking my end had come. When it didn't, I emerged to find the Titan hunched to the ground, the ruby carbuncles on its hide flaring an angry red. It stared up, almost defiantly, at the being of ash and fire and slag, and a plume of smoke issued from the holes in its skull.\n\nI thought a blazing spell was coming, but the Titan only raised its head to lower it again. In deference? Begrudging respect? It was only then that the molten god—whatever it was—touched the dirt with its feet."
msgstr ""

#: 51188213-0-2755
msgctxt "51188213-0-2755"
msgid "The New Lord"
msgstr ""

#: 21337012-0-2754
msgctxt "21337012-0-2754"
msgid "It's been weeks. Months? They say that time flows with demented cadence in the realms of Oblivion. When I get out of here—if I get out of here—the world will have moved on. I pray that, however much time has passed, my husband and the residents of Whisper Grove remain safe.\n\nIt would be a fitting end for all I've given. I am weary, in bone and soul, and this contest is far from finished.\n\nWriting helps."
msgstr ""

#: 51188213-0-2754
msgctxt "51188213-0-2754"
msgid "How Long?"
msgstr ""

#: 21337012-0-2639
msgctxt "21337012-0-2639"
msgid "By the Derisive Necromite\n\nMephala! Webspinner! Teacher of the Secret Arts! Queen of the Eight Shadows of Murder! Though others may reign over us, deep in the night we still hear your whisper!\n\nAnd we do not forget.\n\nIn Oblivion you keep your secrets, and the secrets of all those entangled in your webs of subterfuge and semblance. The Spiral Skein is your realm, and like Nirn, in its center is a Tower: the Pillar Palace of Mephala, whose true name is too awful to be uttered.  \n\nSpun 'round this pillar, like spokes, are the Eight Strands of the Skein. To each its own space, and to each space its sin. \n\nFirst is a cavern of plinths and pedestals. Each is a lie, for they pretend to hold up the sky—and the sky is the greatest lie of all. \n\nSecond are the chambers of envy, for compared to the cavern above they are cramped and confined, and therefore they hate the cavern.\n\nThird are grottoes alluring and seductive, for their walls and ceilings glow like a million stars that sing a song of love. But the glowing lights are maggots, and the song they sing is decay. \n\nFourth are the tunnels of fear, for they are eternally dark, and where there is darkness, there is dread. \n\nFifth are the halls where fair is foul and foul is fair, and every belief is a betrayal. \n\nSixth is the arena of murder, for ever shall betrayal be followed by murder. \n\nSeventh are the arcades of avarice and appetite, for contained therein are all things mortals would kill or die for. \n\nEighth is the flaming skein of fury, for as death comes to all mortals, therefore all treasures are lies. \n\nThis is the Spiral Skein. The tower is One. The strands are Eight. The lessons are Forever."
msgstr ""

#: 51188213-0-2639
msgctxt "51188213-0-2639"
msgid "Rumors of the Spiral Skein"
msgstr ""

#: 21337012-0-2464
msgctxt "21337012-0-2464"
msgid "Esteemed Leader,\n\nOur camp, in the clearing set between where the water spills from Mire Falls, has already achieved exciting results. \n\nNot only have we intercepted a dispatch from Aldcroft, but we've also captured a Lion Guard scout! \n\nIf we wait long enough, perhaps King Casimir will wander in and surrender!\n\n—Leeza of the First Planting"
msgstr ""

#: 51188213-0-2464
msgctxt "51188213-0-2464"
msgid "Leeza's Bloodthorn Report"
msgstr ""

#: 21337012-0-2463
msgctxt "21337012-0-2463"
msgid "Esteemed Leader,\n\nOur camp, in the shadow of Tangle Rock, has produced excellent results! \n\nAlready, the great thorns twist toward the sky and corrupt the swamp. \n\nSoon, this land will be ours!\n\n—Sardok of the Second Planting"
msgstr ""

#: 51188213-0-2463
msgctxt "51188213-0-2463"
msgid "Sardok's Bloodthorn Report"
msgstr ""

#: 21337012-0-2347
msgctxt "21337012-0-2347"
msgid "A hundred and twenty numbered ages in the void that fated folk had grown deep-schooled in evil. Then the Bright Gods resolved to punish those faithless spirits, and shatter the unruly caitiffs, those huge, unholy scathers, loathsome to the Light. They repented exceedingly that they had gazed upon Oblivion, and seen there the first of dark kin, and welcomed them as brothers and sisters.\n\nThe Principalities of Victory beheld how great was the wickedness of the wayward spirits, and saw that they were bold in sin and full of wiles. They resolved then to chasten the tribes of Daedra, and smite darkkind with hammer and hand.\n\nBut ever shall Darkness contest the Light, and great were the Powers that breathed the void and laid waste upon one another, and no oath might bind them, so deep were they in envy and perfidy. For once the portals are opened, who shall shut them upon the rising tide?"
msgstr ""

#: 51188213-0-2347
msgctxt "51188213-0-2347"
msgid "The Waters of Oblivion"
msgstr ""

#: 21337012-0-2244
msgctxt "21337012-0-2244"
msgid "Finally, the altar is prepared and all is in readiness. Tonight, the hordes of Oblivion shall be loosed on the unsuspecting fools in the Pact army!\n\nOh, to be near when the otherworldly beasts descend. How I would savor their pain, their cries of horror, their dying screams. Grand Warlord Sorcalin balked when I proposed this mission, refusing to ""stoop to consorting with Daedra."" So I have undertaken it on my own initiative!\n\nLong have I studied the lore and denizens of those foul lands. I know well the means by which the Daedra are commanded and controlled. There is no room for error when beasts of such power are concerned, and I shall make none.\n\nTonight, one obstacle to the Dominion's conquest of Cyrodiil will be removed. The Covenant is next!"
msgstr ""

#: 51188213-0-2244
msgctxt "51188213-0-2244"
msgid "Time to Strike!"
msgstr ""

#: 21337012-0-2236
msgctxt "21337012-0-2236"
msgid "Molacar,\n\nI agree to your terms and your promise. The gold should go to my parents, in Pell's Gate. I'm not doing this for gold, as you know. If my death might bring Vaermina to save us, I go willingly. But the gold will ease my parents' path through these dangerous times.\n\nI long to be in Her presence.\n\n— Gasparien"
msgstr ""

#: 51188213-0-2236
msgctxt "51188213-0-2236"
msgid "A Promise Made"
msgstr ""

#: 21337012-0-2135
msgctxt "21337012-0-2135"
msgid "It seems fitting that the servant of the Queen of Dawn and Dusk should try to broker peace between the Nedes and the Ayleids. Her realm is between times, between places, and between realities. If I can help two peoples who have such hatred of each other find peace, I will have accomplished something, at least, in my time in this mortal realm. I sense Azura guiding me, and her strength flows within me, but it is her wisdom I need now.\n\n23 Sun's Height\n\nDid I say I needed Azura's wisdom? Nay, I need her patience. Only an immortal could put up with these … people! The Nedes are well-named. Yes, they spent many years shackled and tormented by the Ayleids, but none alive today remember that suffering first-hand! The recompense they demand continues to escalate, even as the pride of the Ayleids swells. I sense they will break off negotiations any day now, and we may go from uneasy peace to outright war.\n\nAh, Azura—keep me from speaking with them! The power of my voice can change their reality, but that would be a bandage on an infected wound. Nothing but true change can allay the anger between these peoples.\n\n27 Sun's Height\n\nThe worst has happened. One of the Ayleids is dead, a messenger killed while running errands. The Ayleids suspect the Nedes and they do not deny it. Rather, they take umbrage … as if the death of one messenger cannot be measured against the long suffering they endured. This will not go well. My voice may be the only answer.\n\n29 Sun's Height\n\nI stand amazed. I did use my voice, but only … adjusted reality somewhat, to forestall conflict. The true miracle came from a Nede and an Ayleid. Both outsiders to the negotiation, they joined together to solve the mystery of the murdered messenger … and found the culprit neither Nede nor Ayleid! A servant of Molag Bal was responsible, his aim to sabotage these negotiations!\n\nThe two heroes have done what I could not. They've brought Nede and Ayleid together against a common foe. I foresee hostilities between these two peoples ended.\n\n2 Last Seed\n\nWith the wedding of the two heroes, the breach has been closed. But I cannot imagine Molag Bal will let this go unchallenged. I will seek an answer … a way to shield these peoples in Azura's name. As long as I live, the Harvester of Souls shall not touch what we have created here today. Azura, give me strength. Let my voice change the world as long as I am in it."
msgstr ""

#: 51188213-0-2135
msgctxt "51188213-0-2135"
msgid "Journal of Culanwe"
msgstr ""

#: 21337012-0-2132
msgctxt "21337012-0-2132"
msgid "You won't regret your pledge to help. Together, we can reclaim Valenwood for the Bosmer!\n\nIf you're reading this, you should already have the requisite list of reagents and know what to do with them. When ready, seek a quiet corner of Grahtwood where you won't be disturbed. Perform the ritual when ready. It's simple—elegant. As Valenwood was before the Dominion polluted it.\n\nHircine will hear our call! The more who call out to him, the louder our voice. Together, we'll hunt—until all left in Valenwood are Bosmer.\n\n—Calahawn"
msgstr ""

#: 51188213-0-2132
msgctxt "51188213-0-2132"
msgid "What Comes Next"
msgstr ""

#: 21337012-0-2082
msgctxt "21337012-0-2082"
msgid "Commander Attius:\n\nI expect you to hold the garrison at all costs. You can and should leverage the captives as hostages if it comes to that. Should the unthinkable occur, instruct your men to fall back across the bridge to the crypts. I have given Battlemage Papus instructions on how to summon the ""gifts"" left buried in the pass so long ago. The garrison will not fall, our lord will see to that.\n\nGlory to Molag Bal,\n\n— Septima Tharn\nMagus-General, Imperial Seventh Legion"
msgstr ""

#: 51188213-0-2082
msgctxt "51188213-0-2082"
msgid "Orders for Attius"
msgstr ""

#: 21337012-0-1931
msgctxt "21337012-0-1931"
msgid "Heed my commands, Diabolist Vethisa, servant of the Shadowed Path!\n\nHigh have you risen in our ranks. Succeed in the task I lay upon you and you will rise higher still. Fail and you will die in agony.\n\nThe Lord of Darkness has revealed to me that an ancient relic lies hidden beneath the soil of southern Cyrodiil. The collapse of the Empire enables us to search for it unimpeded. With this relic in hand, I will lead the Shadowed Path in conquest of the Imperial City and all of Cyrodiil!\n\nYour task is to search the cave called Pothole. Do not take this task lightly. Volcatia and Volgo search for this relic elsewhere. Whoever brings it to me will bask in my favor forever.\n\nI give you command of a Circle of the Shadowed Path. Use these minions harshly, spare no effort regardless of the cost.\n\nDo not fail me.\n\n— Dreadlord Naucratius"
msgstr ""

#: 51188213-0-1931
msgctxt "51188213-0-1931"
msgid "Letter to Vethisa"
msgstr ""

#: 21337012-0-1930
msgctxt "21337012-0-1930"
msgid "Listen well, Volgo, for yours is the most difficult task I lay upon any of my Diabolists.\n\nThe Lord of Darkness has revealed to me that an ancient relic lies hidden beneath the soil of southern Cyrodiil. The collapse of the Empire enables us to search for it unimpeded. With this relic in hand, I will lead the Shadowed Path in conquest of the Imperial City and all of Cyrodiil!\n\nTo you I assign the cave of Nisin. If the relic is there, you must find it. But be wary of the Dremora seeress Barasatii. Avoid openly opposing her or her minions, but do not allow her to claim the relic. It must come to me.\n\n— Dreadlord Naucratius"
msgstr ""

#: 51188213-0-1930
msgctxt "51188213-0-1930"
msgid "Letter to Volgo"
msgstr ""

#: 21337012-0-1926
msgctxt "21337012-0-1926"
msgid "Heed my commands, servant of the Shadowed Path!\n\nHigh have you risen in our ranks. Succeed in the task I lay upon you and you will rise higher still. Fail and you will die in agony.\n\nThe Lord of Darkness has revealed to me that an ancient relic lies hidden beneath the soil of southern Cyrodiil. The collapse of the Empire enables us to search for it unimpeded. With this relic in hand, I will lead the Shadowed Path in conquest of the Imperial City and all of Cyrodiil!\n\nYou are to scour the cavern known as Haynote. Pulverize every rock, crack open every seam—every effort must be made to uncover the relic. Do not return without it.\n\nI give you command of the Circle of the Shadowed Path formerly ruled by Theurgist Thelas. She is no longer in my favor. Repentance is her lot now, to ensure that she survives to face my continued displeasure.\n\nDo not fail me.\n\n— Dreadlord Naucratius"
msgstr ""

#: 51188213-0-1926
msgctxt "51188213-0-1926"
msgid "Letter to Diabolist Volcatia"
msgstr ""

#: 21337012-0-1880
msgctxt "21337012-0-1880"
msgid "By Scholasticus Incognitus\n\nHyrma MORA pado ADA oia NAGAIA aba AGEA cava APOCRA dena GORIA gandra ARCAN\n\nAs everyone in our society knows, the roots of our order are ancient and deep—for are we not the Primeval Seekers? Having spent a season researching ancient manuscripts on Balfiera Island and in the Daggerfall Mages Guild, I can finally provide some details about our hallowed halls of meeting—put some meat on the bones, as it were.\n\nI can now reveal that the original name of our private Ayleid sanctum beneath Halcyon Lake was ""Bisnensel,"" which meant ""New Water Halls"" in the tongue of the Wild Elves. It was built by a clan of Ayleids who fled the anti-Elven pogroms in Cyrodiil during the early First Era, after the slave uprising of the so-called ""saint"" Alessia. The clan that built Bisnensel came from the Heartland city of Nenalata, which like most Ayleid habitations was built partly above and partly beneath the surface of the land. This plan was copied in miniature when the refugee Elves built Bisnensel, though now only the subterranean halls survive intact. \n\nThe ruler of this Elven clan was named Laloriaran Dynar, though he is far better known by the soubriquet ""Last King of the Ayleids."" He was a notable tactician and general, and you have almost certainly heard of him in connection with the great High Rock victory of the Battle of Glenumbria Moors, in which the invading Alessian horde was broken and turned back to Cyrodiil. \n\nPossibly the most fascinating fact turned up in my researches, at least for us of the Primeval Seekers, is that the use of this site for the worship of Hermaeus Mora actually began many thousands of years ago when it was still occupied by the Ayleids! The leader of this effort was a Wild Elf scholar known as High Priest Uluscant, who established a congregation in Bisnensel that attracted many of the learned and most influential people in the community. As their numbers became more numerous, on their behalf Uluscant quite reasonably requested more of a say in municipal affairs, a request that was unfairly denied by ""King"" Dynar. The ruler had no interest in sharing power with a non-military order of scholars, whom he foolishly thought he could insult with impunity. \n\nWell, this Dynar soon learned that the servants of Hermaeus Mora are not so easily shunted aside! Within a few months of his arrogant rebuff, this ""Last King of the Ayleids"" was deposed. He and his family fled to Balfiera, where he begged refuge of the Direnni, whom he served for the rest of his days as a sort of trained war-dog. \n\nAs history teaches us, the Primeval Seekers always win out in time. It's as the ancient analects say: if knowledge is power, then forbidden knowledge is ultimate power! ""For the desire to know is beyond reckoning, and in recompense, whatever price is named shall be met.""\n\nAE HERMA MORA ALTADOON PADHOME LKHAN AE AI"
msgstr ""

#: 51188213-0-1880
msgctxt "51188213-0-1880"
msgid "Bisnensel: Our Ancient Roots"
msgstr ""

#: 21337012-0-1857
msgctxt "21337012-0-1857"
msgid "I haven't left the cave in a month. The beast stalks me in my dreams, and I can hear him in those first few moments when I wake. The Leader was right, the ritual has done its job. Everyone is having the dreams, I can see it in their faces.\n\nTonight, the change will be on me. I'm frightened … but also thrilled. Naraa … I wish you hadn't been so lovely …."
msgstr ""

#: 51188213-0-1857
msgctxt "51188213-0-1857"
msgid "Initiate's Third Note"
msgstr ""

#: 21337012-0-1856
msgctxt "21337012-0-1856"
msgid "I've been here two weeks, and things are progressing nicely. I'm a lot stronger than I was, mostly due to the heavy lifting and sparring we do. I hurt a lot, but it's no worse than being beaten up at home.\n\nThe Pack Leaders never seem to stop preaching. They're always talking about ""being like the wolf"" and how if we focus, we'll ""transcend our weakness."" They're more like a cult than I thought, but I think I've found a home here. \n\nThere's one pretty young thing … Naraa. She seems to like the look of me. We'll have to see what she thinks after the sparring session next week!"
msgstr ""

#: 51188213-0-1856
msgctxt "51188213-0-1856"
msgid "Initiate's Second Note"
msgstr ""

#: 21337012-0-1855
msgctxt "21337012-0-1855"
msgid "First day as a Wolfpack Initiate! We'll see how the bastards who mocked me at home feel when a feared bandit comes calling. I'm keeping my excitement restrained, because the senior members, the ""Pack Leaders,"" are very stern and serious. I just like having a place where I belong.\n\nTheir obsession with wolves is strange, but … they take things seriously, and I respect that."
msgstr ""

#: 51188213-0-1855
msgctxt "51188213-0-1855"
msgid "Wolfpack Initiate's Notes"
msgstr ""

#: 21337012-0-1835
msgctxt "21337012-0-1835"
msgid "Mighty Lord Hircine, noble Lord Hircine, we come before you in all obeisance and humility, acknowledging your divine authority over the forest and all the lawful prey therein. We invoke you, O Master of the Chase, in your aspect of Alrabeg the Hunter, to look kindly upon the endeavors of these, your worshipers, as we praise you by engaging in the hallowed tradition of the Hunt. \n\nEver do we respect the Law of Fair Hunt, never taking a quarry that had no chance of escape. \n\nEver do we respect the Prey, thanking it for its sacrifice in our worship of you. \n\nEver do we respect the Huntsman, beseeching your permission even as we loose the arrow. \n\nBless us as we hunt, O Hircine. Help us to hunt with honor, and bring in prey both lawful and bountiful."
msgstr ""

#: 51188213-0-1835
msgctxt "51188213-0-1835"
msgid "Invocation of Hircine"
msgstr ""

#: 21337012-0-1735
msgctxt "21337012-0-1735"
msgid "Agent: How does it feel to be abandoned by the Pact.\n\nHilka: The Pact didn't abandon me. Thragof did.\n\nAgent: You really do hate him, don't you?\n\nHilka: No more than he deserves.\n\nAgent: Meaning?\n\nHilka: Meaning he's an incompetent idiot who couldn't lead a Khajiit to moon-sugar.\n\nAgent: And the rest of your command?\n\nHilka: Well, if they were bright we wouldn't be here, would we?"
msgstr ""

#: 51188213-0-1735
msgctxt "51188213-0-1735"
msgid "Hilka's Interrogation Transcript"
msgstr ""

#: 21337012-0-1734
msgctxt "21337012-0-1734"
msgid "Agent: Hello again, Hald.\n\nHald: Stay away from me.\n\nAgent: Careful, Hald, you'll hurt my feelings. Especially after you were my guest for, what was it? Eight weeks?\n\nHald: I've nothing else for you. I gave you everything then. Just let me go.\n\nAgent: After how useful you were before? Come now, Hald. You and I both know our arrangement only ends when I say it does."
msgstr ""

#: 51188213-0-1734
msgctxt "51188213-0-1734"
msgid "Hald's Interrogation Transcript"
msgstr ""

#: 21337012-0-1611
msgctxt "21337012-0-1611"
msgid "I dreamed of the treasure again last night. I have no doubt about it now: Hermaeus Mora himself is speaking to me, leading me to it. I've spent my family fortune searching for tomes of power across Tamriel, and my coffers are nearly empty. But I must push on. It's nearly within my grasp.\n\nAnd when I have the knowledge of Apocrypha, I will no longer need to bow to the usurper Tharns. They will bow to me."
msgstr ""

#: 51188213-0-1611
msgctxt "51188213-0-1611"
msgid "Graccus' Journal, Volume I"
msgstr ""

#: 21337012-0-1546
msgctxt "21337012-0-1546"
msgid "Magistrate Sulma,\n\nWe appreciate your offer of gold, but the Withered Hand trades in the currency of corpses. Provide one corpse for every ten gold in your offer, and we will spare the city of Bergama. \n\nAcquire the corpses by whatever means you prefer, stow them in your basement, and we will periodically pick them up. \n\nIf this arrangement does not suit you, we will simply harvest corpses in Bergama ourselves.\n\n— Alasan"
msgstr ""

#: 51188213-0-1546
msgctxt "51188213-0-1546"
msgid "Note from Alasan"
msgstr ""

#: 21337012-0-150
msgctxt "21337012-0-150"
msgid "My hand cramps writing in this tongue. The syntax is pathetic, and the conjugation maddening. But it is the tongue the Black Worm uses. I must adapt. \n\nIt has been centuries since I last walked these halls. There's the spot where my father taught me the Rite of Destruction. There's the stone where I performed my first sacrifice. And of course, there is the rip that swallowed us whole. \n\nHow many years were we trapped in Oblivion?  How long was it before we turned on each other, consuming our brothers and sisters? I alone survive, blessed by Molag Bal for my ruthlessness. Now my lord has chosen me to guide this Black Worm back to Silaseli and repurpose our work.\n\nWhen the Worm told me the halls were filled with castoff men, descendants of our slave stock, I was incensed. My first thought was to wipe out the whole lot. But then I had a thought: If one could be persuaded to reopen the rip, even briefly, the Black Worm could use that as an entry into SIlaseli, avoiding any eyes on the surface. \n\nOne of the Worm's agents found the ideal man for this task. A simple promise of immortality, and his fate was sealed. Once the Worm entered, rounding up the slaves was a simple matter. The creatures will provide an ideal fuel for my lord's Planemeld."
msgstr ""

#: 51188213-0-150
msgctxt "51188213-0-150"
msgid "Vantir's Journal"
msgstr ""

#: 21337012-0-149
msgctxt "21337012-0-149"
msgid "The God of Schemes blesses us. The Lord of Brutality strengthens us. The Harvester of Souls grants us everlasting power. Mortal hosts cannot stand against us.\n\nThe ritual of summoning shall lend us unlimited servants for our domination. Our faith in Molag Bal gives us control over them. We are his chosen servants; his select among a favored few. Our slaves shall bow down before us. They will make our desires their reality.\n\nThe Daedra are but vessels for our corruption. We shall fill them to bursting and set them free upon the world."
msgstr ""

#: 51188213-0-149
msgctxt "51188213-0-149"
msgid "Stonefire Ritual Tome"
msgstr ""

#: 21337012-0-1393
msgctxt "21337012-0-1393"
msgid "The Withered Hand refuses to cease their pleas. They try my patience. I have no love for those of the living who think themselves rulers of the regal dead.\n\nTheir arrogance wears on me. They should be groveling before those that have passed before them, begging to join the glorious life after death."
msgstr ""

#: 51188213-0-1393
msgctxt "51188213-0-1393"
msgid "They Should Grovel"
msgstr ""

#: 21337012-0-1392
msgctxt "21337012-0-1392"
msgid "More of those fools from the Withered Hand approached me today.They entreat me for assistance despite the number of their emissaries I have feasted upon. The easy prey is nice, but I begin to miss the rush of the hunt.\n\nI feel that enough of my power has returned to me that soon I may stray from this cave in search of an unsuspecting meal."
msgstr ""

#: 51188213-0-1392
msgctxt "51188213-0-1392"
msgid "Note Written in Blood"
msgstr ""

#: 21337012-0-1376
msgctxt "21337012-0-1376"
msgid "Enclosed you will find a lock of Hizurrdo's fur. Just remember, there is more than one way to skin a Khajiit."
msgstr ""

#: 51188213-0-1376
msgctxt "51188213-0-1376"
msgid "We Have Control"
msgstr ""

#: 21337012-0-1375
msgctxt "21337012-0-1375"
msgid "Once the amplification crystals are in place, we can begin the process. The amplification crystals are only needed for the possession of Greenhill. Once the dro-m'Athra have gained their foothold here, the artifact will allow them to spread their influence throughout all of Reaper's March. \n\nStill, we should try to keep the crystals active for as long as we can. The more villagers the dro-m'Athra can possess, the quicker they will be able to spread their influence."
msgstr ""

#: 51188213-0-1375
msgctxt "51188213-0-1375"
msgid "The Amplification Crystals"
msgstr ""

#: 21337012-0-1374
msgctxt "21337012-0-1374"
msgid "Anchorite Gaius,\n\nOur spies determined that a couple of Khajiit named Ezreba and Hizurrdo are the closest bonded pair in Greenhill. We have captured Hizurrdo. With his life in the balance, Ezreba will almost certainly do anything we ask. She will be our agent in Greenhill and allow us to place the amplification crystals and begin the possessions. \n\nYour servant, \nAtia"
msgstr ""

#: 51188213-0-1374
msgctxt "51188213-0-1374"
msgid "To Anchorite Gaius"
msgstr ""

#: 21337012-0-1347
msgctxt "21337012-0-1347"
msgid "Patriarch: Offered curses, threats. No useful information. Died during interrogation.\n\nOlder Male: Claimed Chief Tazgol has intense fear of scorpions. Likely fabrication intended to reduce pain. Died during interrogation.\n\nOlder Daughter: Broke quickly. Showed promise. Sadly, knew nothing. Died after interrogation.\n\nOlder Son: Killed self before interrogation could commence. Sloppy. Must remember to acquire new manacles.\n\nYoungest Son: Revealed hidden entrance beneath great hall. Possible link to library. Will keep alive until story is verified.\n\nMorning Addendum: Verified son's story."
msgstr ""

#: 51188213-0-1347
msgctxt "51188213-0-1347"
msgid "Drusilla's Notes"
msgstr ""

#: 21337012-0-1313
msgctxt "21337012-0-1313"
msgid "M'lady, \n\nAs you requested we've been looking for a new place for the faithful to congregate. We believe we have found a place, west of Firsthold along the coast.\n\nWe've consecrated it in the master's name, and await your benediction to make the crude place our own.\n\nIn his name."
msgstr ""

#: 51188213-0-1313
msgctxt "51188213-0-1313"
msgid "A Discarded Missive"
msgstr ""

#: 21337012-0-1275
msgctxt "21337012-0-1275"
msgid "Sentulus,\n\nOver the years, I have recruited dozens to the ranks of the Supernal Dreamers, but none of my recruits have made me nearly so proud as you have. The experiment in Koeglin Village appears to have met with significant success. Your work there has inspired us all and indeed caught the attention of our divine mistress. Vaermina has sent some of her most potent minions to help spread our influence in Stormhaven. Powerful Daedra known as ""Omens"" are working behind the scenes in places of power across this kingdom to mimic your achievement. With their aid, we will ensure that the Daggerfall Covenant is plunged into a nightmare from whence it will not be able to return. \n\nThe task with which you have now been charged is unchanged, but no less critical.  We will need hordes of scamps, clannfear, and Dremora to plague these lands and perpetuate the waking nightmare our mistress has envisioned. Make efforts to recruit local citizens to our cause. If they will not join us, they may be used as vessels or blood sacrifices to aid in the summoning of Daedra. \n\nIn Vaermina's dark name,\n\nNightcaller Chartrand"
msgstr ""

#: 51188213-0-1275
msgctxt "51188213-0-1275"
msgid "Letter to Sentulus"
msgstr ""

#: 21337012-0-1246
msgctxt "21337012-0-1246"
msgid "Fellow Dreamers,\n\nI want to remind you all of the importance of exercising caution and good judgment in maintaining security at our encampments in Gavaudon.  Because of sloppy behaviors among our colleagues in Menevia and Alcaire, we now have a sect of Azura's followers actively working against us, aided by a representative of King Emeric, whom we hoped would not learn of our presence for some time yet.\n\nDue to this situation, our timeline must be accelerated. We must work quickly and efficiently, but also intelligently. Perform the tasks you have been assigned and take precautions to ensure these newly emerged enemies do not get the opportunity to intervene. \n\nOn the positive side, we have succeeded in destroying Azura's shrine at the Weeping Giant, and I have now come here to Aphren's Hold where we will find more relics to aid in our cause. Follow my example. We conducted careful research and reconnaissance before coming here to ensure that our encampment will be secure and our objectives will be achieved. You should do the same.\n\nNow, more than ever, our Mistress looks to us to stay strong, be ever-vigilant, and to assert her will. I hope you prove to be up to the challenge and I hope to see you all soon in Wayrest. \n\nSupernally Yours,\n\nOverdreamer Chartrand"
msgstr ""

#: 51188213-0-1246
msgctxt "51188213-0-1246"
msgid "Overdreamer Chartrand's Orders"
msgstr ""

#: 21337012-0-1229
msgctxt "21337012-0-1229"
msgid "Vaermina!\n\nDream of a thousand dreamers!\n\nRevelations of endless elation!\n\nBeacon for lost souls.\n\nBliss for strong souls.\n\nMadness for weak souls.\n\nVaermina!"
msgstr ""

#: 51188213-0-1229
msgctxt "51188213-0-1229"
msgid "Dream of a Thousand Dreamers"
msgstr ""

#: 21337012-0-1228
msgctxt "21337012-0-1228"
msgid "I've found him. Hircine speaks—to me!\n\nI must not falter. I must not yield to the injustices I have suffered! Though they all turn against me, I will not give in!\n\nI return to <<1>>. There, in the haunted place where I was born, I shall find the power Hircine promised me! With it, I will forge a new way, a new story!\n\nAs I rise, as I tear through the remains of Silvenar's city and self, <<2>> will come to me, Green Lady or no! She will have no choice! For Hircine is my Huntsman, and I his faithful Hound!"
msgstr ""

#: 51188213-0-1228
msgctxt "51188213-0-1228"
msgid "I Must Not Falter"
msgstr ""

#: 21337012-0-1224
msgctxt "21337012-0-1224"
msgid "Something's not right here.\n\nWe've been hearing noises from the catacombs. We've been … seeing things. Spectres. Apparitions. Forms gathered before the dawn. \n\nI came here to investigate. I am going to find answers, or I will die trying.\n\nI wrote this in case I don't make it back. If you're reading this, whatever is haunting this tomb has probably killed me. You should go before it kills you, too.\n\nI say this so you can make your peace with Azura before it happens to you. Turn back now. Look to the dawn. See her radiant majesty. It's not too late to save your life, and more importantly, your soul.\n\nDarkness is all around you. Turn back to the dawn."
msgstr ""

#: 51188213-0-1224
msgctxt "51188213-0-1224"
msgid "Look to the Dawn"
msgstr ""

#: 21337012-0-1222
msgctxt "21337012-0-1222"
msgid "Dreamers! Our time has come!\n\nYou have traveled far to walk with us, brother. You have walked far, sister, wandering across a broken world of lies and suffering.\n\nYou have journeyed long to chant with us. We shall extol the beatific wonders of Vaermina! May her dream be unending!\n\nStormhaven lies before us, and we must share her dream. Those who can see, those who will awaken will join us. We call to the humble and the mighty. Those who are weak, those who are blind, she will cast down into madness.\n\nGo forth! \n\nTo the tumultuous strife of Wind Keep, go forth!\n\nTo the tears of the suffering in Weeping Giant, go forth!\n\nSpread the word! Herald the dream!\n\nWe will gather our armies of dreamers. Then we will all return to the city of lies: the city of Wayrest. The heresy of the Eight will be torn down. The dreamers will ascend! Wayrest will become our City of Dreams!\n\nOur new age has begun. We will join her in eternity.\n\nAll praise the name of Vaermina!"
msgstr ""

#: 51188213-0-1222
msgctxt "51188213-0-1222"
msgid "Dreamers Our Time Has Come"
msgstr ""

#: 21337012-0-1221
msgctxt "21337012-0-1221"
msgid "In dreams, we awaken.\n\nHer reveries call to us. From across Tamriel, her dreams have shown us a true world, a far better world than the one you know.\n\nVaermina lights the sky of our world! Vaermina is the stars of our world! Her thousand truths are a thousand lights in the night sky!\n\nThe wakeful world is full of suffering and starvation. It is a world of lies. We have come from all corners of this broken world to gather as dreamers of a new brighter age.\n\nShe has called us here to Stormhaven! She has awakened us to a better world! We will leave this world of lies behind us!\n\nSome cannot comprehend these simple truths. They do not understand her dreams as we do, for they are not true dreamers. She calls to the mighty and the humble, yet those who are found wanting are cast down into madness.\n\nAwaken, sleeper! Ascend, dreamer! Seek her in dreams, and join us! \n\nWe await you."
msgstr ""

#: 51188213-0-1221
msgctxt "51188213-0-1221"
msgid "In Dreams We Awaken"
msgstr ""

#: 21337012-0-1143
msgctxt "21337012-0-1143"
msgid "By the Sinistral Apprentice\n\nNote to self: Remember, the most important thing is to pay homage to the flames of the Deadlands first. \n\n- - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -\n\nAs discussed in Liminal Bridges, the transpontine circumpenetration of the limen requires the cooperation—implicit or otherwise—of a Daedra Lord.\n\nUnfortunately for the conjurer of modest means, the process described is costly, highly esoteric, and impossibly dangerous. Fortunately for the practically-minded practitioner of conjurational studies, there is another option.\n\nDregs of the Deadlands have been known to offer the use of existing Sigil Stones in crossing the traverse. Though the purposes of said beings must be regarded with wary suspicion, it is frequently possible to engage in transliminal studies with minimal risk to one's person, especially if one's go-between is supplied with sufficient motive.\n\nThe Deadlands, of course, are filled with searing heat and suffocating ash. But if you find a way to quench these things, their secrets—and those of Oblivion itself—lie at your fingertips.\n\nTake heed, then, and read well of what fates befell those who first attempted contact with these domains.\n\nFirst, there was the scholar Daron, who thought the sheer power of elemental flame would be enough to initiate contact with the Dremora of the Deadlands. Though his attempt was impressive—indeed, the fire instilled in the walls of his hovel would go on to spark one of the worst wildfires in Valenwood history—it ultimately proved futile. His ashes were never recovered.\n\nBelieving Daron was on to something, Olpion of Firsthold sought to insulate the flames with compacted earth. By all accounts he nearly succeeded, but when his chambers burst from the walls of the Crystal Tower, his apparatus lost focus, collapsing the gateway upon itself.\n\nIn the end, it was the Naga, Avumar, whose multifarious approach led to the final revelation. Once the flames were ignited, it was Avumar who thought to use an earthen vessel to convert the immense energy into steam. Once her boiler reached sufficient temperature, she was able to converse with a Dremora of some power on the other side.\n\nRelieved, no doubt, at her success in the face of her predecessors' failure, Avumar quickly agreed to the terms of the Dremora's contract. An ominous decision, it turns out, that ultimately led to the fall of Thorn.\n\nTake care, therefore, in your attempts to contact the Deadlands, for good seldom comes out of agreements made in haste with the creatures who call it home."
msgstr ""

#: 51188213-0-1143
msgctxt "51188213-0-1143"
msgid "Tome of Daedric Portals"
msgstr ""

#: 21337012-0-1100
msgctxt "21337012-0-1100"
msgid "By Sigillah Parate\n\nPROPHECY is her province, and that which is seen by the Night Sky Queen must eventuate, however dimly it may appear to mortal foresight. For mortals are not all given the gift of Crystal Vision, nor can they always endure knowledge of the truth.\n\nDAWN is the time of imminence, when Azura touches us with wisdom and purpose. It is then we speak the Supplication for Guidance, and tremble in fear that it may be answered.\n\nROSE is Her color and Her flower, and Moonshadow Her abode as Risen is the sun. Tend we then by midday our mortal necessities, conserving always some part of ourselves for when the sun slides low.\n\nDUSK is when we turn our hands to Azura's commands. Then we praise Her with our dark evening acts, and glorify Her with chastening of noncompliance. \n\nFATE is the Book that She writes in to inscribe our worth and deserts. For by our acts do we earn Her regard or disdain, and read our destiny in Her prophecy."
msgstr ""

#: 51188213-0-1100
msgctxt "51188213-0-1100"
msgid "The Five Points of the Star"
msgstr ""

#: 21337012-0-1096
msgctxt "21337012-0-1096"
msgid "Martine,\n\nYour ships are more than adequate to transport our agents. All you need to do is deliver the cargo. Once night falls, we'll emerge from the crates and use Leveque's maps to get close to King Casimir.\n\nAngof will be pleased with the chaos caused by Casimir's death! The kingdom's leaderless ranks will offer the Bloodthorns little resistance. Overcoming the south will be easy and Glenumbra will be ours. Rest assured that you will be compensated very well for your loyalty to the Bloodthorn's cause.\n\nSee that those crates are not disturbed. The agents inside must stay hidden until the time is right. If they are discovered, I will perform the deed myself and then come back for you. Do not fail us.\n\n—Verrik"
msgstr ""

#: 51188213-0-1096
msgctxt "51188213-0-1096"
msgid "Verrik's Note"
msgstr ""

#: 21337012-0-1069
msgctxt "21337012-0-1069"
msgid "<<1>>,\n\nOur cause would be glad to have one so well versed in magic. Your former employer was foolish not to put your talents to better use, but his loss is our gain.\n\nJoin us in Abamath, but be warned! There is no going back. Cut ties with your former life. Distractions will not be tolerated in your service to the Black Worm.\n\n																																							— <<2>>"
msgstr ""

#: 51188213-0-1069
msgctxt "51188213-0-1069"
msgid "There Is No Going Back"
msgstr ""

#: 21337012-0-1049
msgctxt "21337012-0-1049"
msgid "Aera Earth-Turner:\n\nYou have lost those dear to you. But there are ways you may be reunited with them. Old ways, proven through time and blood.\n\nJoin us. All we ask is information about the Pact's movements. Provide those, remain loyal, and we will reunite you with your loved ones.\n\nIn Mannimarco's name,\n\n—	Thallik Wormfather"
msgstr ""

#: 51188213-0-1049
msgctxt "51188213-0-1049"
msgid "There Are Ways"
msgstr ""

#: 21337012-0-1002
msgctxt "21337012-0-1002"
msgid "We must maintain a count of the population of Narsis. With so many already fled to Mournhold, the number we have to work with has dwindled significantly.\n\nIf we abduct too many of the villagers, the Llodos plague won't have enough victims to take hold of, nullifying the entire purpose of this experiment. Luckily, the nobles who believe everything will be just fine refuse to leave their houses and remain ripe to contract the plague.\n\nAs it stands, there should be enough people remaining to spread the plague efficiently once the pieces fall into place. Even so, we must continue to maintain our list. One miscount could affect the potency and reduce how far we can spread the disease."
msgstr ""

#: 51188213-0-1002
msgctxt "51188213-0-1002"
msgid "A Tally of Villagers"
msgstr ""